Central Banks Pull 635 Tonnes of BIS Gold in Last Year, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-07-08T00:44:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-08/central-banks-pull-635-tonnes-of-bis-gold-in-last-year-ft-says.html
The  Bank for International
Settlements  said central banks have withdrawn 635 tonnes of gold
from the so-called “bank for central banks” in the past year,
the largest amount to be taken out in more than 10 years, the
Financial Times reported, citing the BIS’s annual report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 